We need to show `x_{m+1} ∈ supp P_{m+1}`.
We know `P_{m+1} = Vector.push <$> P_m <*> ($ᵗ α)`.
So, `P_{m+1}` is the distribution of `fun w hw ↦ fun v hv ↦ Vector.push w v` applied to `P_m` and `($ᵗ α)`.
The support of this distribution should be the set of all `Vector.push w v` where `w ∈ supp P_m` and `v ∈ supp ($ᵗ α)`.
